title: Ex-Bulldog Hickel Makes Team USA Roster
text:
Ex-Bulldog Hickel Makes Team USA Roster 
By Zach Schneider Ex-Bulldog Hickel Makes Team USA Roster October 1, 2015 Updated Oct 1, 2015 at 7:03 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Former University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) forward Zoe Hickel has been named to the United States roster ahead of next month's Four Nations Cup, it was announced on Thursday afternoon. 
Hickel won a gold medal with Team USA at the IIHF World Championships this past April, which was her first time representing the nation. 
in her four seasons with UMD, Hickel totaled 46 goals and 47 assists while also serving as the team's captain in the 2014-15 campaign. 
The 2015 Four Nations Cup will be held Nov. 4-8 in Sweden.
